      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. SMELLY HALLE continues to race well, filling the minors at the last three starts, the latest at Addington in 30.32. Having first start on this course but does drop slightly in class. Looks the testing material here. 5. RATHER CONVINCED finished in the minors last time but only a few starts back broke the clock when winning over 457m at Manawatu, taking a Class 2 in a convincing 25.81. Top win three back and rates a key player again. 7. ZARA JEM settled down midfield and held her position to the line when finishing 4th (17.40) at Addington. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings five times from eight starts. Key runner on best form. 1. ALL OVER ROVER boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip. Should be running home stronger than most.\",\"runners\":[3,5,7,1],\"exclusive\":false}",
